# Frontend Test Selectors

## Use `data-testid` for custom rendered elements

When the component renders SVG, canvas, or other non-text elements that could collide with icon libraries (e.g. Lucide), add a `data-testid` and select with `screen.getByTestId()`.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD -- grabs the first <svg>, which may be a Lucide icon
document.querySelector("svg")

// ✅ GOOD -- targets exactly the chart SVG
screen.getByTestId("nw-chart")
```

## Avoid bare `getByText` for short/common strings

If the text could appear in both mock data and UI controls (dropdowns, labels), `getByText` will throw "Found multiple elements". Use a more specific query.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD -- "Checking" appears as both an account name and a subtype option
screen.getByText("Checking")

// ✅ GOOD -- scope to a specific container or use getAllByText
within(screen.getByRole("combobox")).getByText("Checking")
screen.getAllByText("Checking")
```

## Prefer role-based queries when possible

`getByRole`, `getByLabelText`, and `getByPlaceholderText` are more resilient to UI changes than `getByText`. Fall back to `getByTestId` only when no semantic query fits.
